From a89c5b7947e323f3fc1b10a141e8c5080bdbbafd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Henke <henke.mike@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 08:28:16 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 03/10] fix(task-session-manager): fire onJobTerminal from
 injected completion + review cleanups

- Call onJobTerminal when an injected completion marks a background job
  terminal, so the orchestrator is notified even when session.idle fires
  after the job is already completed.
- Dedupe onJobTerminal per taskID to prevent double-fire.
- Extract findByParent() helper to remove peek/take duplication.
- Scope fallback phantom-drop to a single phantom job.
- Rename onTerminalJob -> onJobTerminal; drop redundant shouldManageSession
  guard; add typeof guard on board-part overwrite; add peek JSDoc and
  isFallbackInProgress JSDoc; split the over-packed phantom-drop test;
  add a test asserting onJobTerminal fires on injected completion.
